# Introduction

The NHS remains one of the most important public healthcare systems in the UK, operating under the principles of universal healthcare and free access at the point of delivery. However, increasing pressure on emergency departments has created severe operational challenges, particularly regarding patient waiting times.

The four-hour A&E standard introduced by the UK government aimed to ensure that 95% of patients were admitted, transferred, treated, or discharged within four hours. However, the NHS has failed to meet this target nationally since 2013.

Long waiting times negatively impact:

* patient outcomes
* quality of care
* patient satisfaction
* operational efficiency
* hospital sustainability

This project investigates the root causes of prolonged waiting times and explores how business analytics techniques can support better patient flow management and healthcare decision-making.

