# Methodology

The project combined descriptive, inferential, predictive, and prescriptive analytics techniques.

## Descriptive Analytics

Descriptive analysis was used to examine:

* historical waiting time performance
* patient demographics
* operational trends
* hospital capacity pressures

## Correlation Analysis

A Spearman correlation matrix was developed to assess relationships between operational variables and waiting time performance.

## Multiple Regression Analysis

Non-linear multiple regression models were used to determine which operational and demographic variables significantly contributed to prolonged waiting times.

Regression models examined:

* workforce levels
* bed occupancy
* deprivation levels
* age groups
* gender
* ethnicity
* department type

## Time-Series Forecasting

Seasonal ARIMA (SARIMA) modelling was applied to forecast future NHS A&E delays.

The forecasting process included:

* trend analysis
* seasonality decomposition
* stationarity testing
* SARIMA diagnostics
* future demand forecasting

