# Recommendations

## Dynamic Resource Allocation

Implement real-time operational dashboards monitoring:

* bed occupancy
* patient arrivals
* staffing levels
* emergency demand patterns

This would support faster operational decision-making during peak demand periods.

## Predictive Workforce Planning

Forecasting models should be used to predict seasonal demand surges and optimise staffing allocation.

Flexible staffing strategies and emergency staffing pools may reduce pressure during winter periods.

## AI-Assisted Patient Prioritisation

Machine learning-assisted triage systems could improve patient prioritisation based on:

* clinical urgency
* medical history
* presenting symptoms

This may reduce inequities and improve patient flow efficiency.

## Patient Education and Demand Management

Public education campaigns encouraging use of:

* GP services
* telemedicine
* minor injury units

could reduce unnecessary A&E attendance.

